From 491f4e9064eec1fed4ac7b3fb2ff237622461cc0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:22:08 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] Fill in the remaining shell request handlers

A request arriving for a NULL slot in a libwayland interface vtable
crashes the compositor, so every advertised request needs a handler
even if we do not really support the feature yet.

- xdg_wm_base / zxdg_shell_v6: create_positioner (stub positioner
  storing nothing yet) and pong.
- xdg_surface / zxdg_surface_v6: get_popup, currently a stub that
  immediately sends popup_done; real popup windows are future work.
- xdg_toplevel / zxdg_toplevel_v6: resize (interactive, with edge
  tracking), show_window_menu (no-op), set_fullscreen and
  unset_fullscreen (refused by re-sending a configure without the
  fullscreen state); guard NSWindow delegate callbacks against use
  during destruction, and send configures eagerly.
- wl_shell_surface: pong, resize, set_transient and set_popup
  (treated as toplevel), set_fullscreen (no-op), set_maximized,
  set_class.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
